A fakir was sitting on the bank of a river.

Someone asked Baba what are you doing?

The fakir said - I am waiting for the whole river to flow so that I can cross it again.

That man said - Baba, what are you talking about... you will never be able to cross the river while waiting for the full water to flow.

Fakir said - This is what I want to explain to you people that you people who always keep saying that once the responsibilities of the house are fulfilled, then I will offer Namaz, keep beard, perform Hajj, serve...
Just like the water of the river will not end, we have to make a way to cross this water, in the same way life will end but the tasks and responsibilities of life will never end....

Keep praying......
Please send it to someone before letting it go

Man changes house 

 change clothes

 changes relationships

 Friends change, still why are you upset??

 Because he doesn't change himself,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,

 Make a habit of offering Namaz five times a day,,,,,,,.

 Just thinking that who knows, you are listening to this azaan for the last time.

Do you know whether your God is calling you for the last time,,,?

 90% people do not forward this message,,,

But you must do it, there should be no delay in spreading the religion of Allah.

Undoubtedly  the one who engages in the works of Allah, Allah himself engages in his works..```

*Do not consider the month of travel as bad and unfortunate*
,
Safar is the name of a month in the Islamic calendar, some people believe that this month is very inauspicious, calamities/baddies are sent in it, and to prove their point, they also present some false traditions. Apart from these things, it is also said that in this month one should not get married, should not travel, should not start any good or new work, 13th of this month is considered bad, Ankhari Mercury of this month. Whether it is considered good or bad, some people also go to gardens on this Wednesday. It is said that on this day, when Hazrat Muhammad (Sallallahu Alaihi Sallam) recovered from fever, he went to the garden. All these things are completely wrong in the light of Quran and Hadith.

The reality is that before the advent of Islam, the illiterate people of Arabia believed that the month of Safar was a month full of calamities and ill-luck, but when Hazrat Muhammad (Sallallahu Alaihi Sallam) brought the message, he said (There is a hadith in which You have said that there is no such thing as Safar, here you mean that the month of Safar is not a month of misfortune or trouble. (Bukhari/Muslim)

There is no argument in Shariat that the month of Safar is unlucky or full of calamities, no day or month is considered unlucky in Islam.

Therefore, in this month, travel, get married, do happy things, do new things. The marriage of Hazrat Ali (Radi Allahu Anhu) and Hazrat Fatema (Radi Allahu Anha) also took place in this month. If it was forbidden to marry in this month or it was an inauspicious month full of troubles, would Prophet Muhammad (Sallallahu Alaihi Sallam) have done this?

Whatever we have been hearing since childhood, it is not necessary that everything is correct, earlier people did not have many facilities to learn knowledge, but now there are many scholars, there are videos of big scholars on the internet. If you want to learn or know anything, now it is very easy for us. There should be a yearning in the heart to learn the truth.

Note: *The evils that are revealed in this world throughout the year, Allah Almighty names them Zad in the month of Safar*.

 *(Malfoozat Khwaja Nizamuddin Rahmatullah Alaihi Safa-185)*

May Allah guide us all on the right path, Ameen.

*Lesson Number {214}*

 *Misunderstanding about backbiting.*

Undoubtedly, backbiting is a very big sin. And everyone knows this. But what is the definition of backbiting? Who is called Gibat? If you read only the low opinions of people about it, you will know how much wrong understanding has been created among people about gossip.
When a person is being abused in a Majlis and is stopped, people say low things about slander.

 I am not slandering but showing about Fulana person.

 I have no intention of gossiping.

 Don't misunderstand it, I am just showing its true form.

 Do not call this backbiting. This evil actually exists in it.

 I am just saying about it, my intention is not to gossip.

 All the things that are said about the above gossip are things that people have made up from themselves. While the correct definition of backbiting is written below...

* To do wrong to a person in his absence which would be wrong if that person were present.*

One of the reasons for people's misunderstanding about backbiting is not knowing the difference between backbiting and backbiting.

* DIFFERENCE BETWEEN GIBAT AND TOHMAT.*

If the person who is experiencing evil is actually evil in that person or not...?

* If there is evil in reality, then it will be called backbiting.
* If there is no actual evil then it will be called Tohmat.

*Note :-* If a person has such evil in him which causes great harm to others, it is permissible in Shari'ah to show that person's evil to the other person only with the intention of protecting the other person from harm.

*Quran and Hadith mention many strict oaths and threats about backbiting, so it is very necessary to avoid this Kabirah (major) sin.*
